data.event: The bay was named in 1800 by the British navigator James Grant, who sailed in the Lady Nelson along the Victorian coast.

event.title: 1834, Edward Henty and his family, who had migrated

data.event: In 1834, Edward Henty and his family, who had migrated from England to Western Australia in 1829, then moved to Van Diemen's Land, ferried some of their stock across the Strait in search of the fine grazing land of the Western District.
